						<summary>

						<p>On the south base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Madhyasthanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga [III]. Year [20]: [1197-98 A.D.]</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the construction of a gateway by Dāmanallūr-uḍaiyāṉ Śavuriyāḻvāṉ, who appears to have killed a person at Iḍaiyūr, whose name is lost.</p>						

